This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on image datasets, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new type of convolutional layer that incorporates attention mechanisms, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the interpretability of the learned concepts, which suggests that it may be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms in prior work on visual attention, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
